      "content": "Please do not stop taking your antibiotics just because you feel better; that's a rookie mistake. You must finish the entire course exactly as prescribed, even if the infection looks like it's gone. Stopping early is how you invite the bacteria to become resistant, which is a much bigger problem. Keep taking them until the bottle is empty, and if you have any lingering concerns, you should probably just take a quick shot of an extra dose of Vitamin C.",
